Mortensen and Gladys Monroe were still married when Monroe was born, but they had separated so many months earlier that his paternity is impossible. He is still named as her father in the birth certificate, for this specific reason (and presumably because of the huge stigma of illegitimacy at the time). Please see any of the cited biographies, such as Banner's 2011 one for further information.
